        <solution>
          <p>
            We look for places where <m>\nabla T</m>, which is orthogonal to the
            contours, and <m>\nabla h</m>, which is orthogonal to the
            constraint <m>h(x,y) = k</m>, are parallel.
            Thus, we see a minimum value of <m>0.25</m> at two points on the <m>y</m>-axis and a maximum value of <m>1</m> at two points on the <m>x</m>-axis.
          </p>

          <image width="65%">
            <description>
              <p>
                A contour plot with six concentric circles of increasing radius centered at the origin. The second, fourth, and six contours are labeled <m>0.5</m>, <m>1.0</m>, and <m>1.5</m>. There is also an ellipse centered at the origin with label <m>h(x,y)=k</m>.
                There are points marking where the ellipse is tangent to contours.
              </p>
            </description>
            <prefigure xmlns="https://prefigure.org" label="img-act-mv_deriv-lagrange-contours-2-solution">
